Long post...but truly all in love ❤️ Last night I went to bed with a heavy heart...reading so many post about fear of this disease. PLEASE HEAR MY HEART! I’m not trying you sell anything!!!! Please let me be so clear about this. My story is, I was diabetic with an A1C of 13, high blood pressure so high, I wasn’t going home (I was at a dr. appt.) I was going to the hospital if I couldn’t get it down, an hour and a half later and two pills later I could leave and directed to go straight home. I also heard the words “your going to have a stoke” if you don’t lose weight and start taking care of yourself! But all I heard was stroke. SO I UNDERSTAND fear. In 7 months I was off my meds (Metformin and Glipizide) and lost 45 pounds. My Doctor asked me to get the word out... so I am, because I have a voice today to do this. Had I lived with the fear and not learned what to do I might not be able to share this. Can I guarantee my results? NO! Have I helped people and got them off meds/insulin? YES. This is what’s important...whether you talk to me, a dietitian...we have to eat! I see people wanting to take drastic measures and stop eating, that’s the worst thing you can do. That’s like sugar throwing a party in our bodies! or taking a pill to get the weight off while still eating what in most cases got us to be diabetics. I urge you to seek help and know there are great plans out there to help you, and teach you how and what to eat. Please seek the help, you don’t have to live in fear and the biggest thing, it doesn’t have to be hard. I’m telling you all this because I lived in fear, and it was waisted worry. ❤️

Stay away from these items well cause a drastic raise in blood sugar. Cakes, pies, donuts, any kind of candy, ice cream, soda pop, most bread, unless it’s whole-grain keep to a minimum. I am seriously going to get myself star stickers, weird but apparently my body is being controlled by my 3, 6, and 9 year old trauma selves that don't like taking our meds. Today is day 2 of actually remembering to take them. Seriously nothing helps me remember. I don't even remember to eat. One would think i would because I have fasting high blood sugar,  and it has put me on death's door to many times to count.  2 things I have lerned since recently staring to work with a family nurse practitioner who specializes in diabetes management.  1. Fatty Liver is actually caused my too much blood sugar in the body. 2. Fructose causes Fatty Liver Disease. Our body has a fail safe if we eat to much natural occurring Fructose we get sick. But there is no fail safe for synthetic produced Fructose, so our body turns it into sugar with attaches to our liver and causes fatty liver.  The more you know. And yet for some reason as much as i know how dangerous diabetes is, I cant seem to make myself realize juat how dangerous it is. Maybe it is because I have a bunch of other diseases that are shutting my body down, that I am not processing the severity of this disease. Sorry for the long post. Just getting my late night thoughts out there before my meds finally kick in and make me sleep.

Someone please help me. I don’t know what to do. A week ago Friday I worked an 8 hour day at the office. When I left work on Friday. I was fine. I woke up Saturday with numb hands and feet, by Sunday it was my arms and legs. But, I “passed our at home stroke test” so I figured I’d wait till Monday. Monday, my mouth, my whole body and pelvic region were numb so off to ER I went. The tests they ran all came back normal so they sent me home with a peripheral neuropathy diagnosis. I saw my GP Tuesday and Thursday due to weakness and pain and he ordered different bloodwork and got me in for an MRI on Tomorrow. I will also let you know I am a stage 3B, 12 year breast cancer survivor (yay me!) I do not have a neurologist yet. Does PN manifest in a weekend. I am so weak I’m unable to work. Spend most of my time in bed. I feel like I am carried by phantom legs when I walk to bathroom.  My blood work came back from GP everything looks great. That brings me to tears because I am not great. I don’t know what to do.  My hand is so weak I can’t open a hair clip. My feet feel freezing most of the time. Pins and needles numb. They did CT, x-rays, and blood. I am going back to GP (3rd time in a week) probably just to cry and say help me.
